Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 02:27:55 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] Add pyramid/cone volume/surface area and
 trapezoid/rhombus templates: 4 new certified templates
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Closes real gaps identified when precisely re-auditing chapter
coverage: pyramids and cones had ZERO coverage (Chapter 12 sections
12.3/12.5), and trapezoids/kites had ZERO coverage (Chapter 7 section
7.5) despite the rest of Chapter 12 (prism/cylinder/sphere volume,
sphere surface area) and Chapter 7 (angle relationships, diagonal
bisection) already being certified.

New problem types (geometryProblemTypeRegistry.js v1.0.11 -> v1.0.12):
- pyramid_or_cone_volume
- cone_surface_area
- trapezoid_midsegment
- rhombus_diagonal_angle

New certified templates (geometryTemplateRegistry.js v1.7.0 -> v1.8.0):
- pyramid_or_cone_volume_calculation: square pyramid ((1/3)*s²*h, pure
  integer, height always a multiple of 3) or cone ((1/3)*π*r²*h,
  radius always a multiple of 3) — both scenarios guaranteed to
  produce an exact integer coefficient by construction.
- cone_surface_area_calculation: reuses the SAME certified
  PYTHAGOREAN_TRIPLES list already used by
  pythagorean_theorem_missing_side and right_triangle_trig_ratio, so
  the slant height (hypotenuse of the radius/height right triangle)
  is always an exact integer — surface area = πr(r + slant height)
  always reduces to an exact integer π-coefficient.
- trapezoid_midsegment_calculation: two scenarios (find the
  midsegment from both bases, or find a missing base from the
  midsegment and the other base), both constructed by picking the
  ANSWER value first and deriving the given quantities around it —
  avoids any parity/rounding edge case entirely, the same technique
  already proven safe for triangle_proportionality_missing_segment.
- rhombus_diagonal_angle_measure: a rhombus's diagonal bisects its
  vertex angle exactly in half; the half-angle is picked first (1-89°)
  and the full vertex angle derived from it (always even, always a
  valid positive angle).

New variable generator functions (geometryVariableGenerator.js
v1.9.0 -> v1.10.0), verified with 40 seeds x 4 templates (160 runs)
including independent mathematical re-derivation per run — notably
re-verifying the Pythagorean relationship r² + h² = slantHeight²
directly from the raw values for every cone_surface_area run, not
trusting that reusing the certified PYTHAGOREAN_TRIPLES list was
sufficient on its own.

Full regression: all 57 certified templates (53 previous + 4 new)
confirmed supported by the generator.

Still pending in this same feature: Solver, Distractor Engine, and
Prompt Renderer support for these 4 new templates (next commit).
